content:
Page 1

A GitHub Pages site built from the /docs folder using an automated front-end build process with minified HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Page 2

As well as being minified, the JavaScript is transpiled to version ES2015 for wider browser support.

Page 3

Site assets, such as images and favicons are copied across to the /docs folder during the build process. These files must be specified in the scripts section of the package.json file.

Page 4

The original source files (index.js, files in js-modules/, style.css with nesting, etc.) remain in the project root for easier development and editing.

Page 5

Important: When publishing to GitHub Pages, make sure the Pages setting is configured to serve from the /docs folder on the main branch.
